        "description": "This project details how to create a \"pikapika\" style animation, which involves using long exposure photography and a light source to create animated light doodles. The method described includes using a coat hanger model to allow a single person to create the animation.",
        "steps": [
            "Learn the basics of long exposure light painting, referencing external resources provided.",
            "Construct a model out of coat hangers to serve as a reference point for the light doodles. This is especially useful when working alone.",
            "Set up a camera with long exposure settings (e.g., \"STARRY SKY\" mode). Take a series of photos, each time posing the coat hanger model and creating a light doodle around it.",
            "Import the images into video editing software and set each image to a very short duration. Sequence the images to create the animation. Loop the animation and add music, if desired.",
            "Consider painting the coat hanger model flat black to reduce reflections and improve the clarity of the final animation."
